[[Image:Swiss_Olympic_training_base.jpg|thumb]]海拔{{convert|1856|m|ft}}的瑞士奧林匹克訓練基地進行的高原訓練]]
'''高原訓練'''是一種通過在高[[海拔|海拔]]地區對[[運動員|運動員]]進行訓練從而提高其耐力的方法，進行高原訓練的地點的最佳海拔是{{convert|2400|m}}以上，但是實際上因為在這種高度難以找到合適的訓練場地，一些高原訓練也會在較低一些的地區進行。在高原訓練時，[[缺氧|缺氧]]環境可以促使運動員體內的[[紅血球|紅血球]]、[[血紅蛋白|血紅蛋白]]增加，新陈代謝也會加快。<ref name=Formenti>{{cite journal |first1=F|last1=Formenti |first2=D |last2=Constantin-Teodosiu |first3=Y |last3=Emmanuel |first4=J |last4=Cheeseman  |title=Regulation of human metabolism by hypoxia-inducible factor |journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the USA |volume=107 |issue=28 |pages=12722–12727 |date=June 2010 |pmid=20616028 |pmc=2906567 |doi=10.1073/pnas.1002339107 |displayauthors=4|last5=Dorrington |last6=Edwards |first6=L. M.|last7=Humphreys |first7=S. M. |last8=Lappin |first8=T. R. J. |last9=McMullin |first9=M. F. |last10=McNamara |first10=C. J. |last11=Mills|first11=W. |last12=Murphy |first12=J. A. |last13=O'Connor |first13=D. F. |last14=Percy |first14=M. J. |last15=Ratcliffe |last16=Smith|first16=T. G. |last17=Treacy |first17=M. |last18=Frayn |first18=K. N. |last19=Greenhaff |first19=P. L. |last20=Karpe |first20=F. |last21=Clarke|first21=K. |last22=Robbins |first22=P. A.|bibcode=2010PNAS..10712722F }}</ref><ref name="pmid16497842">{{cite journal |last1=Wehrlin |first1=JP |last2=Zuest |first2=P |last3=Hallén |first3=J |last4=Marti |first4=B |title=Live high—train low for 24 days increases hemoglobin mass and red cell volume in elite endurance athletes |journal=J. Appl. Physiol. |volume=100 |issue=6 |pages=1938–45 |date=June 2006 |pmid=16497842 |doi=10.1152/japplphysiol.01284.2005 |url=http://jap.physiology.org/content/100/6/1938.long |accessdate=2009-03-05 |archive-date=2017-06-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170630201656/http://jap.physiology.org/content/100/6/1938.long |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="pmid17805094">{{cite journal |last1=Gore |first1=CJ |last2=Clark |first2=SA |last3=Saunders |first3=PU |title=Nonhematological mechanisms of improved sea-level performance after hypoxic exposure |journal=Med. Sci. Sports Exercise |volume=39 |issue=9 |pages=1600–9 |date=September 2007 |pmid=17805094 |doi=10.1249/mss.0b013e3180de49d3 |url=http://meta.wkhealth.com/pt/pt-core/template-journal/lwwgateway/media/landingpage.htm?an=00005768-200709000-00023 |accessdate=2009-03-05 |archive-date=2013-04-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130430170806/http://meta.wkhealth.com/pt/pt-core/template-journal/lwwgateway/media/landingpage.htm?an=00005768-200709000-00023 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Acclimatization>{{cite journal|last1=Muza|first1=SR|last2=Fulco|first2=CS|last3=Cymerman|first3=A|title=Altitude Acclimatization Guide|journal=US Army Research Inst. of Environmental Medicine Thermal and Mountain Medicine Division Technical Report|issue=USARIEM–TN–04–05|year=2004|url=http://archive.rubicon-foundation.org/7616|accessdate=2009-03-05|author=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090423042451/http://archive.rubicon-foundation.org/7616|archive-date=2009-04-23|dead-url=yes}}</ref> 而在一些較低海拔地區，儘管有時[[氧氣|氧氣]]含量並未減少，但通過降低[[氣壓|氣壓]]、[[氣體分壓|氣體分壓]]依然可以達到訓練耐力的效果。<ref name="pmid8904608">{{cite journal |last=West |first=JB |title=Prediction of barometric pressures at high altitude with the use of model atmospheres |journal=J. Appl. Physiol. |volume=81 |issue=4 |pages=1850–4 |date=October 1996 |pmid=8904608 |doi= |url=http://jap.physiology.org/content/81/4/1850.long |accessdate=2009-03-05 |archive-date=2017-05-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170516012614/http://jap.physiology.org/content/81/4/1850.long |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altitude.org/high_altitude.php|title=Online high-altitude oxygen and pressure calculator|publisher=Altitude.org|access-date=2015-06-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100201060010/http://www.altitude.org/high_altitude.php|archive-date=2010-02-01|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

在無法找到合適的高海拔訓練場所時，仍可以使用[[高原帳篷|高原帳篷]]和[[呼吸訓練器|呼吸訓練器]]等設備來達到類似的效果。而閉氣訓練，即在運動時刻意降低呼吸頻率，也可以起到相似的作用。<ref>Xavier Woorons, "[http://www.hypoventilation-training.com/Activity.html Hypoventilation training, push your limits!] {{Wayback|url=http://www.hypoventilation-training.com/Activity.html |date=20170717193234 }}", Arpeh, 2014, 176 p (ISBN 978-2-9546040-1-5)</ref>

== 歷史 ==
[[File:13-07-23-kienbaum-unterdruckkammer-33.jpg|thumb]]
高原訓練的相關研究始於[[1968年夏季奧林匹克運動會|1968年夏季奧林匹克運動會]]之後，當時這場運動會舉行于海拔{{convert|2240|m}}的[[墨西哥城|墨西哥城]]，所有的耐力項目得分都遠低於平常，而衝刺等需要爆發的厭氧運動項目卻屢破紀錄。<ref>{{cite web|title=Mexico 1968 Summer Olympics|publisher=Olympics.org|url=http://www.olympic.org/mexico-1968-summer-olympics|access-date=2015-06-18|archive-date=2020-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128081901/http://www.olympic.org/mexico-1968-summer-olympics|dead-url=no}}</ref> 實際上在運動會之前就有預測這種高海拔場所會對運動員的表現有所影響，而此後也終於得到了證實。<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Ward-Smith|year=1983|title=The influence of aerodynamic and biomechanical factors on long jump performance|journal=Journal of Biomechanics| volume=16| pages=655–658| doi=10.1016/0021-9290(83)90116-1|pmid=6643537| first1=AJ| issue=8}}</ref>

